dcterms:description: A labeled dataset containing approximately 891,000 real-world conversation sessions, where each session's turns are annotated by human annotators as either satisfying (SAT) or dissatisfying (DSAT). The dataset is used to model user satisfaction in conversational agents.
dcterms:title: Dsup

dcterms:description: An unlabeled dataset consisting of real-world session data that is about twice the size of Dsup. It includes all session turns and is used to augment the training data for user satisfaction prediction without specific annotations.
dcterms:title: Dunsup
